BREAKING: PASCHAL NJOKU Justice Okon Abang of the Federal High Court sitting in Abuja on Friday dismissed a suit filed by the Legal Defense and Assistant Project (LEDAP) praying the court to declare the seat of Senate President, Bukola Saraki; Speaker of House of Representatives of Yakubu Dogara and over 50 affected National Assembly members vacant over their defection in 2018. The suit among other reliefs sought for an order asking the affected senators to refund all remuneration paid them starting from the day they defected from one political party to the other. Delivering judgement in the suit, Justice Abang held that though the plaintiff had merit and was good, however, the court held the plaintiff lacked the locus standi to institute the case. Details soonâ€¦..